akas: Diario di una nerd superstar Italy
akas from release info: Diario di una nerd superstar Italy

1.title: Prank Amateurs
1.plot: Senior pranks wreak havoc while Jenna's resolution to stop thinking about Matty is tested when she overhears a disturbing secret.

2.title: Short Circuit Party
2.plot: Jenna causes an accident at school that has surprising results. Meanwhile Matty must deal with the aftermath of his confrontation with Jake.

3.title: Jenna in Wonderland
3.plot: While Jenna gets a taste of popularity, Matty struggles with being shunned. Meanwhile, Jake goes after a new girl, and Ally hosts a sex toy party.

4.title: Now You See Me, Now I Don't
4.plot: Senior Yearbooks are out. Jenna's depressed to see her senior superlative, but what will Matty say in her yearbook?

5.title: The Dis-Engagement Dinner
5.plot: Jenna's forced to throw Tamara a party to celebrate her fake engagement. Meanwhile, Gabby reveals a secret about Matty that sends Jenna in search of the truth.

6.title: Don't Dream It's Over
6.plot: When Tamara accuses Jenna of being a relationship saboteur, Jenna confronts her ex-boyfriends with surprising results.

7.title: The Big Reveal
7.plot: Jenna wants to reveal the truth to Matty, but will her loved ones stop her?

8.title: An Indecent Promposal
8.plot: It's promposal season at PHHS and Jenna receives some surprising news.

9.title: Say No to the Dress
9.plot: Jenna is determined to have a dream prom despite many obstacles.

11.title: The Graduates
11.plot: Everyone tries to make the last night of high school count.

12.title: Holding on and Letting Go
12.plot: High school is finally over and everyone is preparing for college.

13.title: I'm the Kind of Girl Who Found Her Voice in College
13.plot: Everyone arrives back from high school and Jenna feels weird that everyone is changing around her.

14.title: WTF Happened Last Year?
14.plot: Jenna reveals what happened to her and the rest of the gang in the last year-what caused the deep freeze between Matty and Jenna, what sparked the friendship between Sadie and Tamara, and how Jake and Lissa rekindled their romance.

15.title: The Friend Connection
15.plot: Jenna avoids a new relationship in order to connect with her co-workers. Meanwhile, Tamara throws a chic birthday party for Sadie that leaves more than one partier feeling less than celebratory.

16.title: Best Friends for Never
16.plot: In an effort to make Idea Bin a friendlier place for herself, Jenna hooks Tamara up with an internship but quickly discovers that working with friends can be a recipe for disaster.

17.title: Fireworks
17.plot: Jake secures shifts for Jenna and Tamara at the country club for the Fourth of July, but Sully's plans for an after-hours party on the golf course lead to some dramatic fireworks.

18.title: Digging Deep
18.plot: After their Fourth of July fun, Jenna and Matty continue to rekindle their friendship by throwing a party for Jake, at least until Jenna's latest Idea Bin post threatens to unravel it all.

19.title: Girls Gone Viral
19.plot: Jenna tries to decide between success at Idea Bin and her tenuous friendship with Matty. Jake has an unexpected hookup, and Sadie and Sergio find themselves baring more than ever before.

20.title: Misadventures in Babysitting
20.plot: Jenna volunteers to babysit, and receives some unexpected help in Matty. Meanwhile, Lissa learns the secret to being a Palos Hills mom, and Tamara and Sadie are in over their heads at a rich-kid clambake.

21.title: Living in Sin
21.plot: Jenna takes things with Luke to the next level, and Tamara's debt comes back to bite her.

22.title: Home Again, Home Again
22.plot: A fight with Luke pushes Jenna to sign up for her camp reunion - and towards reconnecting with Matty.

23.title: Second Chances
23.plot: Help from Luke lands Jenna an important meeting at SCU, Tamara comes clean to Patrick about her money woes, and Matty enlists Sadie's help to get him out of the doghouse with Lacey.

24.title: Happy Campers. Happier Trails
24.plot: In the season 5 finale, Luke helps Jenna land an important meeting at SCU, Tamara admits she has money problem to her boyfriend, and Jenna has important decisions to make that include choosing to attend an SCU event or her camp reunion; and Luke or Matty.

1.title: Pilot
1.plot: Wallflower Jenna's teen angsty journal and a bizarre accident result in her folks thinking she's suicidal. Plus she's in the cast from hell. How will this affect her school life? and more importantly her relationship with the cute but clueless boy hunk Matty.

2.title: Knocker Nightmare
2.plot: Jenna finally gets her cast off and looks forward to regaining her anonymity but when a boob photo is sexted around school, that becomes unlikely.

3.title: The Way We Weren't
3.plot: Jake and Lissa are having a three month anniversary party. When Matty tells Jenna she should come, Jenna is uncertain if that's way of saying he's ready to go public with their relationship.

4.title: The Scarlet Eye
4.plot: Jenna's friends convince her that it's time to DTR - define the relationship. And what better time than at the big school bonfire?

5.title: Jenna Lives
5.plot: Matty's told Jenna that he's not ready for a relationship. So why does he seem to be having one with new girl, Jenna Plus? And what's with the kid selling Jenna Lives T-shirts?

6.title: Queen Bee-atches
6.plot: Jenna's mother wants to become a member of the "PV moms" and so Jenna must make a good impression on the members. Unfortunately, the president of the PV moms is Jenna's nemesis Sadie Saxton's mom. And Matty has a gig there as a waiter.

7.title: Over My Dead Body
7.plot: Drunk Driver awareness day is coming up at school and guidance counselor Val is determined that Jenna will play Dead Stacey in her play. Meanwhile Jake tries repeatedly to ensure that Jenna is not upset about their kiss.

8.title: The Adventures of Aunt Ally and the Lil' Bitch
8.plot: Jenna's Aunt Ally comes for a visit and decides to throw a "kick-ass kegger" for her "Lil' Bitch". The thing is, things always get out of hand when Aunt Ally is around.

9.title: My Super Bittersweet Sixteen
9.plot: Jake confesses to Liss that he kissed Jenna. After Liss slaps Jenna, Liss and Jake end up in Counselor Val's office.

10.title: No Doubt
10.plot: Jake tries to make-up it up to Liss for kissing Jenna but when Liss allows Sadie to help set the terms, things get mean. Meanwhile Matty finally asks Jenna out on a real date but the remoteness of the restaurant has Jenna wondering is she's still his stealth girlfriend.

11.title: I Am Jenna Hamilton
11.plot: Jenna is now officially with Matty and expects him to ask her to the Winter Formal. However, Matty only hints at it and Jake asks her properly. What is she to do? At the same time, Lissa decides to make Jake jealous to win him back.

12.title: Fateful
12.plot: Jenna is going to the Winter Formal with Jake (plus Tamara), but Matty's friends convince him to fight for Jenna. Is there still time? Lissa has moved on from Jake, but Sadie still has her loyalty - or does she?

1.title: Resolutions
1.plot: Since the Dance, Jenna's been with Jake, but hasn't declared herself as his girlfriend on her blog. Now it's almost New Year and everyone will gather at the party Matty is hosting. And Jenna is given until midnight to make up her mind.

2.title: Sex, Lies and the Sanctuary
2.plot: Turns out that a security camera has been pointed at the Sanctuary for quite some time, meaning that there is a disc containing secrets of several people, including Jenna. To get the disc, Ming has to make friends with "her people".

3.title: Three's a Crowd
3.plot: It's National Anti-Bullying Week. Val hires a new student councilor. Lacey has a surprise for Kevin. Jenna realizes she has lingering feelings for Matty - and Matty doesn't even want to let go of her. So, Jenna seeks advice from... Sadie?

4.title: Are You There God? It's Me, Jenna
4.plot: Jenna's burden drives her to enlist for Lissa's church retreat. But Sadie will not risk Jenna making friends with Lissa. Val hears Kevin is single and goes after him - through Lacey. And has Kyle the Stalker founded a new club?

5.title: My Love Is a Black Heart
5.plot: It's Valentine's Day. Matty is dating a freshman. Tamara is going to the Black Hearts Party, but so is Ricky - with another girl. Lacey is feeling romantic, but Mike isn't. Jenna and Jake's romantic dinner comes with an awkward surprise.

6.title: What Comes First: Sex or Love?
6.plot: When Jake surprises Jenna with his "I Love You", Jenna must decide how she feels and why she hesitates to say it back. Could sleeping with Jake help her make up her mind?

7.title: Another One Bites the Dust
7.plot: It's Ally's wedding day. Jenna is assigned to flower girl duty, and Tamara becomes the wedding planner's assistant. Sadie is a bridesmaid. Lacey was hoping to rekindle things with Kevin, but he isn't coming. But "her Ben" is. "Her Ben"?

8.title: Time After Time
8.plot: Jenna's decided that she loves Jake and wants to say it too. However, her duties as "flower-bitch" at her mom's best friend's wedding are getting in the way, particularly when her mom's old boyfriend shows up as one of the guests.

9.title: Homewrecker Hamilton
9.plot: Watch an all new season of Awkward Tuesdays at 10:30p/9:30c on MTV. Haunted by her break-up and make-up with the boys, Jenna privately struggles with how to untangle her twisted love life until.... an unexpected text brings all her drama to the spotlight.

10.title: Pick Me, Choose Me, Love Me
10.plot: Jenna's shocked to catch her parents together in the morning. Lacey's shocked to find out everyone knows she wrote the letter. Jenna's now a taste-maker. Ming's back with the Mafia. But what about Jake and Matty? And does Sadie have herpes?

11.title: Once Upon a Blog
11.plot: When Jenna's private blog is made public the reaction at school is not as expected, but, there is collateral fallout.

12.title: The Other Shoe
12.plot: Jenna has chosen Matty. But he's about to work at a camp instead of going to Europe for the summer with Jenna. Becca is forcing Fred away from Ming. Lissa wants Jake back, and Tamara just wants someone. But why is Ricky avoiding Sadie?

1.title: Cha-Cha-Cha-Changes
1.plot: After a summer ensconced with Matty, Jenna is worried that she's lost touch with her BFF's Tamara and Ming. Everyone suspects that Sadie is pregnant. Although they're back from Europe, Jake and Tamara can't seem to stop practicing their French. Jenna finds herself in a creative writing class with a tyrannical teacher.

2.title: Responsibly Irresponsible
2.plot: While everyone is dealing with the death of a classmate, Jenna is also dealing with the after-effects of her recent pregnancy scare.

3.title: A Little Less Conversation
3.plot: Jenna worries that her relationship with Matty may be on the rocks, and tries to avoid having "the talk" after her pregnancy scare.

4.title: Let's Talk About Sex
4.plot: When Jenna's dad learns that she's on the pill he reacts badly and calls Matty's parents. Meanwhile Sadie must deal with how an injured Lissa affects the cheer squad.

5.title: Indecent Exposure
5.plot: When Matty has a fight with his parents and comes to stay at the Hamilton's, Jenna misses having her personal space. Tamara crashes the cheerleaders sleepover and after a ouija board revelation about Ricky's death, learns a little something about Sadie as well.

6.title: That Girl Strikes Again
6.plot: Jenna and the gang crash an upscale Halloween party and Jenna gains a new perspective on her life and friends. Sadie retrieves a golden trophy that she believes is rightfully hers and meets a potential new friend in the process.

7.title: Guilt Trippin'
7.plot: Jenna feels guilty about a school tradition of a dance involving elaborate invites that highlights couples and makes singles feel inferior. Matty learns to dance.

8.title: Rubbed Raw and Reeling
8.plot: Jenna is challenged to read something revealing at a local open mike night but has second thoughts when she finds her parents in the audience. Meanwhile Jake and Matty have a boy's night. New guy Colin likes Jenna's writing and afterwards...

9.title: Reality Check
9.plot: Jenna is conflicted when new guy Collin keeps popping up in her creative writing fantasy assignment. Ming throws down when Becca gets Fred Wu expelled and transferred to a school in Idaho.

10.title: Redefining Jenna
10.plot: Collin invites Jenna to an art opening for a photographer that she and Matty liked but when Matty bails to help Jake with a party that Tamara is co-hosting, Jenna finds out that her interest in Collin is mutual. Lissa confesses that she's convinced that she killed Ricky with second-hand peanut sauce.

11.title: Surprise!
11.plot: After an impulsive make out with Collin, Jenna resolves to end her infidelity before Matty finds out.

12.title: And Then What Happened
12.plot: What really happened at the surprise party, and are Jenna and Matty done for good? Only they know for sure, but all their friends recount the fateful event and try to connect the dots.

13.title: Taking Sides
13.plot: Jenna decides to throw a bbq in the hopes of warming her friends up to her and Collin's budding relationship. But when their support is withheld in more ways than one, Jenna takes drastic measures against her besties.

14.title: The Bad Seed
14.plot: After DEFRIENDING Tamara and Ming, Jenna feels she has nothing left to lose and finds herself in quite a sticky situation.

15.title: A Very Special Episode of Awkward
15.plot: At Val's behest, Mr. Hart's class writes and produces their own after school special, and the cautionary tale they come up with looks awfully familiar.

16.title: Less Than Hero
16.plot: The backlash of Jenna's discord with her friends leads her to a night on the town. But what should have been a night to blow off steam becomes a night she needs to be rescued from.

17.title: The Campaign Fail
17.plot: It's time for Jenna to get back on the straight and narrow, but she's done more damage to her friends and family than a little campaigning can fix. Will they forgive her or will she have to go to extremes to right her wrongs?

18.title: Old Jenna
18.plot: After apologizing to her mom and her friends. Jenna believes she is ready to get back together with Matty.

19.title: Karmic Relief
19.plot: Jenna and her Mom fight to get Val's job back while the Chinese Mafia does some housekeeping. Prom dates are lining up while Jenna waits for the expected invite from Matty.

20.title: Who I Want to Be
20.plot: Jenna is challenged to question who she wants to be in this epic season finale.

1.title: No Woman Is an Island
1.plot: Jenna begins her senior year determined to make a fresh start, but she experiences major humiliation at home and in school. Also, her lingering feelings for Matty challenge her resolve to avoid boy drama and focus on school.

2.title: Listen to This
2.plot: Jenna struggles to communicate with Matty, thinking that his remoteness is about their recent hookup when it is actually about a big discovery he is keeping to himself. Meanwhile Tamara questions Jake's musical talent.

3.title: Touched by an Angel
3.plot: Jenna and Matty try to be friends with benefits, but Matty's focus solely on the benefits leaves Jenna feeling less than friendly.

4.title: Sophomore Sluts
4.plot: Jenna and Tamara have found formidable rivals in the form of the "Sophomore Sluts" for the Spirit Week title, and, more importantly, for Matty and Jake's attention.

5.title: Overnight
5.plot: Jenna and Tamara go on their first overnight college visit, but the outcome is not what they expect. Meanwhile, Lacey craves a college experience of her own and a party at Matty's creates new rivalries and romances.

6.title: Crowning Moments
6.plot: Jenna's got a new college romance, but can't escape the high school drama while stage-managing a male beauty pageant. Meanwhile, Tamara grows more desperate in her attempts to win Jake back.

7.title: After Hours
7.plot: What is planned as an amicable group outing devolves into the night from hell, during which Jenna, who has set Matty and Eva up on a date, realizes that she still might still have feelings for him.

8.title: Prison Breaks
8.plot: In the wake of her fight with Matty, Jenna decides to visit Luke at college, but her plans for a romantic evening go awry. Meanwhile, Matty and Jake spend a night in jail and Tamara has an unexpected hookup.

9.title: My Personal Statement
9.plot: College apps are due and Jenna and Tamara must face the possibility of their separate futures, while Eva plots her own path to keep Matty and Jenna on the outs.

10.title: Snow Job: Part 1
10.plot: Rivalries and romances all come to a head on the Palos Hills High School senior ski trip.

11.title: Snow Job: Part 2
11.plot: Sadie discovers the truth about Eva and tries to open Matty's eyes with Jenna's help. But Eva comes forward before they do it and she also has a big surprise.

12.title: Finals
12.plot: After the dramatic senior ski trip, Jenna tries to focus on her finals but the aftershocks of the Eva's baby bomb threaten a finals failure.

13.title: Auld Lang Party
13.plot: Jenna's plans for a quiet New Year's Eve go awry and evolve into a rocking rager at Ally's house, where everyone gets a taste of something (or someone) new.

14.title: Welcome to Hell
14.plot: Jenna receives a rejection that burns her up inside and has her heading for a meltdown, while Lissa's family's "Hell Tent" takes revelations to a whole new level.

15.title: Bonfire of the Vanities
15.plot: The annual senior bonfire becomes a powder keg when Jenna and Tamara find the boys'girl-rating tradition known as the Phone Book and announce it to the school.

16.title: #drama
16.plot: The battle of the sexes erupts once again when Jenna and Tamara's Dude Database goes viral and reveals a secret that causes friction in their own friendship.

17.title: The New Sex Deal
17.plot: Valentine's Day is looking bleak in the aftermath of PHHS' battle of the sexes, so Jenna takes it upon herself to bring sexy back with a rented party bus.

18.title: Girl Rules
18.plot: Matty's 18th birthday pits Jenna against his new girlfriend Gabby, while Sadie and Tamara's battle for cheerleading dominance yields some very unexpected results.

19.title: Over the Hump
19.plot: Jenna tries to keep everything in balance, but the stress of college applications and boy drama leaves her final Spring Break on the verge of falling apart.

20.title: Sprang Break, Part 1
20.plot: At Ally's rental beach house in Rosarito, Mexico there is enough sun, sand, sex, secrets, and shenanigans to go around.

21.title: Sprang Break: Part 2
21.plot: At Ally's rental beach house in Rosarito, Mexico there is enough sun, sand, sex, secrets, and shenanigans to go around.

imdb.plot outline: "Awkward" is about the specific incidents in our formative years that define us -sometimes for the best and sometimes for the worst. The show centers around fifteen-year-old Jenna Hamilton, who, like many, feels invisible to her peers and desperately wants to find her place--which is hard to do in a day and age where fitting in means standing out. Unfortunately, Jenna's visibility comes on the heels of an accident that gives her a not-so-fun stigma. And while the stigma of her accident could be the curse of her life, Jenna's determined to make it her life's blessing.
imdb.title: Awkward.
plot: An unpopular 15-year-old gains immediate, yet unwanted, popularity at her high school when the student body mistakes an accident she has for a suicide attempt.::tb4000

Awkward is about a girl Jenna who is in high school. Her bff T is the one who gives her good and bad advice. Jenna is faced with many obstacles of sex, friends, guys, and just fitting in. Val is her school counselor who sometimes goes a little over board with her "advice". But MATTY is everything she has ever dreamed of in a boyfriend there's just one thing hey won't take her out in public. Jenna is just trying to survive high school!
